{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5734dacc-4042-4b37-a30f-2bfdc8986f48","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01SAwqZ25CRC98hCefKKHF2p","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Reviewing project files"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01NhusMTgXNe4nnvpuXErdmG","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-31235afb4d4041f59d6919c22a4ae6c4"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-31235afb4d4041f59d6919c22a4ae6c4."}],"interactionId":"8a3f708b-1ae3-48fd-9254-69e56893557d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change when upgrading from MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 to MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0, specifically related to test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes.\n\nLet me look at the files in the working directory to understand the context better, and also think about what I know about this change.\n\nKey change: Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0, Microsoft introduced the \"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" (MTP) as the default test runner, but maintained backward compatibility with VSTest. In MSTest.Sdk 3.x, the `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform` property defaulted to `true` but still supported VSTest discovery.\n\n\nThe critical breaking change is that MSTest.Sdk 4.x completely removed VSTest compatibility—it no longer generates the VSTest entry point or test adapter references that vstest.console depends on for discovery. This means projects upgrading to 4.x can't use vstest.console anymore without explicitly disabling the Microsoft.Testing.Platform integration.\n\nThe solution is either switching CI to use `dotnet test` instead, which works with the new platform, or attempting to restore VSTest adapter generation if that property still exists in 4.x. Let me look at the project files to understand what's actually configured here.","outputTokens":597,"requestId":"4C17:2C626E:CC9657:F7BA00:6A0147FA"},"id":"aeba3378-0e68-4a24-a57b-ca08ee75be6e","times