{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a951112d-f6aa-4387-934e-9008ce17d1e3","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility layer entirely.** The SDK now exclusively uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (MTP) and no longer ships the VSTest adapter that `vstest.console.exe` needs to discover tests.\n\n### What to do\n\n**Option A — Switch your CI to `dotnet test`** (recommended):\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n```\n`dotnet test` now routes through Microsoft.Testing.Platform automatically with MSTest.Sdk ≥ 3.8.\n\n**Option B — If you must keep `vstest.console`**, pin to the 3.x SDK line:\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n```\n\nThere is no property in 4.x to re-enable the VSTest adapter; the removal is intentional and permanent.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8a3f708b-1ae3-48fd-9254-69e56893557d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I can give a clear answer. The issue is that MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest infrastructure entirely. In MSTest.Sdk 3.x, the SDK included the VSTest adapter/runner infrastructure alongside Microsoft.Testing.Platform. In 4.x, the VSTest compatibility layer was removed, so `vstest.console.exe` can no longer discover or run these tests.","outputTokens":307,"requestId":"4C17:2C626E:CCCCDE:F7F94D:6A01480C"},"id":"86576d71-39e5-418f-ae32-898898e3faf8","timestamp":"2026-05-11T03:08:03.726Z","parentId":"5585f735-2bc0-48f7-94ce-1646fd6b061e"}
